defaultWritten evidence submitted by defaultThe Children’s Societydefault&#xa0;defaultAbout The Children’s Societydefault&#xa0;
defaultThe Children’s Society supports nearly 50,000 children and young people every year through our specialist 
defaultservices and children’s centres. We believe in achieving a better childhood for every child but have a particular focus on children who have nowhere else to turn, such as children living in poverty, young refugees, children at risk on the streets, disabled
default children and children in trouble with the law. We seek to give a voice to children and young people and influence policy and practice so they have a better chance in life.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe believe that every child has the right to a decent home that their family can a
defaultfford. We welcome the opportunity to raise our concerns with the committee about the impact that reforms to housing support in the welfare system could have on this.
default&#xa0;
